In a speech delivered on November 26, 2020, President Trump addressed members of the United States military deployed around the world and wished them a happy Thanksgiving. He expressed his gratitude for their service and praised the military's efforts in fighting terrorism and protecting American interests. The President also highlighted the investments made in the military during his administration, including the creation of the Space Force. He then went on to discuss his concerns about alleged voter fraud in the 2020 presidential election, stating that he believes the election was rigged and that there was massive fraud. He expressed his intention to continue challenging the election results and claimed that he had evidence of widespread voter fraud. The President also mentioned his plans to visit Georgia to support the Republican candidates in the upcoming Senate runoff elections. He concluded the speech by suggesting that he may run for president again in 2024 and criticizing the media and big tech companies for what he perceived as biased coverage and censorship.